sections.title: How the population has changed in Malvern Hills
sections.label: Select another area to see how the population has changed

sections.content: In 2020, Malvern Hills was the 28th largest local authority in the West Midlands, with a total population of 79,445. An increase compared with 2019.

sections.title: Largest local authorities in the West Midlands, 2002-2020
Population density in Malvern Hills
sections.content: In 2020, the population density in Malvern Hills was 138 people per square kilometre, which was less than the West Midlands (459), and less than the United Kingdom as a whole (276).

sections.title: Densest local authorities in the West Midlands, 2020
Median age in Malvern Hills
sections.content: In 2020, the median age in Malvern Hills was 51 years, which was older than the West Midlands (40 years), and older than the United Kingdom as a whole (41 years).
